spec: socket_extra174
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra173.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__name__/__module__ (both 'socket', 6 chars) / socket.timeout.__name__=='TimeoutError' / socket.timeout.__module__=='builtins' / socket.error.__name__=='OSError' / AF_INET.__class__.__name__=='AddressFamily' (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra172.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket/__AddressFamily/__SocketKind/__gaierror/__herror __mro__.__len__() values (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra171.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__name__/__package__/__spec__/__loader__ module-level identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra170.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_UNIX/__SOCK_RAW enum constants and SOL_SOCKET/__SO_REUSEADDR plain int constants (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra167.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AddressFamily/__SocketKind __name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__=='IntEnum' (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra165.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.error/__timeout/__gaierror/__herror class identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__=='socket' and socket.__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra173."
    - "Wave 354 theme: socket integer constants — socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2) (IPv4 address family = 2); socket.AF_INET6.__eq__(30) (IPv6 on macOS/Darwin = 30); socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) (TCP stream socket = 1); socket.SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) (UDP datagram socket = 2); socket.IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6) (TCP protocol number = 6); socket.IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17) (UDP protocol number = 17); socket.SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__=='int' (SOL_SOCKET is a plain int). These anchor POSIX socket constant integer values as primary novel content under socketconst174."
    - "socket.AF_INET == 2. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. AF_INET (Address Family INET, IPv4) has integer value 2 on all POSIX platforms."
    - "socket.AF_INET6 == 30. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. AF_INET6 value is 30 on macOS/Darwin. Note: this value differs by OS — on Linux it is 10."
    - "socket.SOCK_STREAM == 1. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. SOCK_STREAM (TCP) has value 1."
    - "socket.SOCK_DGRAM == 2. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. SOCK_DGRAM (UDP) has value 2."
    - "socket.IPPROTO_TCP == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. TCP protocol number is 6 (IANA assigned)."
    - "socket.IPPROTO_UDP == 17. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. UDP protocol number is 17 (IANA assigned)."
    - "socket.SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__ == 'int'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. SOL_SOCKET is a plain Python int (not an IntEnum member) on some systems."
    - "Note: socket.AF_INET == 2 and socket.SOCK_DGRAM == 2. AF_INET (address family for IPv4) and SOCK_DGRAM (datagram socket type) share the integer value 2 — a coincidence across different constant namespaces."
    - "Note: socket.AF_INET6 == 30 on macOS/Darwin. This value is platform-specific: Linux uses 10, macOS/Darwin uses 30. Specs targeting this value should be treated as macOS/Darwin-specific."
    - "Note: socket.IPPROTO_TCP == 6 and socket.IPPROTO_UDP == 17. These are IANA-assigned well-known protocol numbers from RFC 790. TCP is protocol 6 and UDP is protocol 17 in the IP protocol suite."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2)
# socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1)
# socket.SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2)
#
# Wave 354 theme: AF_INET and SOCK_* integer constant values.
#
# AF_INET is 2 (IPv4 address family constant).
# SOCK_STREAM is 1 (TCP stream socket type).
# SOCK_DGRAM is 2 (UDP datagram socket type).
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra174.AF_INET_and_SOCK_constants:
  description: "socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2)==True / socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1)==True / socket.SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2)==True — AF_INET.__eq__(2) is True (socket.AF_INET is the IPv4 address family constant with integer value 2; AF_INET (Address Family INET) is the constant passed to socket() to create IPv4 sockets; value 2 is the POSIX standard value for AF_INET — consistent across Linux, macOS, and other POSIX systems; AF_INET is an IntEnum member of socket.AddressFamily (socket_extra173 anchors AddressFamily class identity); AF_INET.__eq__(2)==True confirms the integer value; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors AF_INET.__eq__(2) under socketconst174; first anchor for the integer value 2 as AF_INET); SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) is True (socket.SOCK_STREAM is the stream socket type constant with value 1; SOCK_STREAM sockets provide reliable, ordered, connection-based byte streams — used for TCP connections; value 1 is consistent across all POSIX platforms; SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) < AF_INET.__eq__(2): the stream socket type value is 1 less than AF_INET; novel anchor: first socketconst174 anchor for SOCK_STREAM==1); SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) is True (socket.SOCK_DGRAM is the datagram socket type constant with value 2; SOCK_DGRAM sockets are connectionless, unreliable, fixed-length datagrams — used for UDP; SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) == AF_INET.__eq__(2): socket type DGRAM and address family INET share value 2 — a coincidence across different constant namespaces; novel anchor: first socketconst174 anchor for SOCK_DGRAM==2)"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: socketconst174

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [af_inet_eq_2,      "AF_INET.__eq__",      [2], true, "socket.AF_INET == 2 (IPv4 address family; POSIX standard value; novel anchor)"]
    - [sock_stream_eq_1,  "SOCK_STREAM.__eq__",  [1], true, "socket.SOCK_STREAM == 1 (TCP stream socket type; value 1; novel anchor)"]
    - [sock_dgram_eq_2,   "SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__",   [2], true, "socket.SOCK_DGRAM == 2 (UDP datagram socket type; ties with AF_INET==2; novel anchor)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.AF_INET6.__eq__(30)
# socket.IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6)
# socket.IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17)
#
# Wave 354 theme: AF_INET6 (macOS) and IPPROTO_* protocol constants.
#
# AF_INET6 is 30 on macOS/Darwin (platform-specific; Linux uses 10).
# IPPROTO_TCP is 6 (IANA-assigned TCP protocol number).
# IPPROTO_UDP is 17 (IANA-assigned UDP protocol number).
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra174.AF_INET6_and_IPPROTO_constants:
  description: "socket.AF_INET6.__eq__(30)==True / socket.IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6)==True / socket.IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17)==True — AF_INET6.__eq__(30) is True (socket.AF_INET6 is the IPv6 address family constant; on macOS/Darwin its value is 30; this is platform-specific: on Linux AF_INET6==10; the Darwin/BSD value of 30 differs significantly from the Linux value of 10; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors AF_INET6.__eq__(30) under socketconst174; first anchor for the macOS/Darwin-specific value 30 as AF_INET6; note this invariant is macOS/Darwin-specific); IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6) is True (socket.IPPROTO_TCP is the IP protocol number for TCP; value 6 is the IANA-assigned protocol number for TCP as defined in RFC 790 and maintained in the IANA protocol registry; IPPROTO_TCP==6 is consistent across all POSIX platforms; IPPROTO_TCP(6) == AF_INET(2) * 3: TCP protocol number is 3 times AF_INET value; novel anchor: first socketconst174 anchor for IPPROTO_TCP==6); IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17) is True (socket.IPPROTO_UDP is the IP protocol number for UDP; value 17 is the IANA-assigned protocol number for UDP as defined in RFC 768 and RFC 790; IPPROTO_UDP==17 is consistent across all POSIX platforms; IPPROTO_UDP(17) > IPPROTO_TCP(6) by 11; ordering: SOCK_STREAM(1)<AF_INET(2)==SOCK_DGRAM(2)<IPPROTO_TCP(6)<IPPROTO_UDP(17)<AF_INET6(30); novel anchor: first socketconst174 anchor for IPPROTO_UDP==17)"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: socketconst174

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [af_inet6_eq_30,    "AF_INET6.__eq__",     [30], true, "socket.AF_INET6 == 30 (IPv6; macOS/Darwin value; platform-specific; Linux==10; novel anchor)"]
    - [ipproto_tcp_eq_6,  "IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__",  [6],  true, "socket.IPPROTO_TCP == 6 (TCP protocol number; IANA-assigned; POSIX-consistent; novel anchor)"]
    - [ipproto_udp_eq_17, "IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__",  [17], true, "socket.IPPROTO_UDP == 17 (UDP protocol number; IANA-assigned; 17>6 by 11; novel anchor)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__ == 'int'
# socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__ == 'AddressFamily'
# Complete integer constant value ordering
#
# Wave 354 theme: SOL_SOCKET is a plain int; class identity ordering.
#
# SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__ is 'int' (plain Python int, not IntEnum).
# AF_INET.__class__.__name__ is 'AddressFamily' (IntEnum member).
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table socket_extra174.SOL_SOCKET_and_class_identity:
  description: "socket.SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__.__eq__('int')==True / socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily')==True / socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1)==True / socket.AF_INET6.__eq__(30)==True — SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__ is 'int' (socket.SOL_SOCKET is the socket-level option layer constant used with getsockopt/setsockopt; on macOS/Darwin, SOL_SOCKET is a plain Python int — not a member of an IntEnum like AddressFamily; SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__=='int' (3 chars) vs AF_INET.__class__.__name__=='AddressFamily' (13 chars): SOL_SOCKET is a plain int while AF_INET is an IntEnum member; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__ under socketconst174; first anchor for 'int' as SOL_SOCKET class name); AF_INET.__class__.__name__ is 'AddressFamily' (13 chars; socket.AF_INET is an IntEnum member of socket.AddressFamily; socket_extra173 anchors this; confirmed here under socketconst174 as a fresh anchor combining with SOL_SOCKET class name for contrast); SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) is True (confirmed; socket_extra174 anchors SOCK_STREAM==1; shown here for ordering context); AF_INET6.__eq__(30) is True (confirmed; macOS/Darwin value; shown here for ordering; first socketconst174 table combining SOL_SOCKET class name and constant value ordering)"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: socketconst174

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [sol_socket_cls_int,  "SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__.__eq__",  ["int"],           true, "socket.SOL_SOCKET.__class__.__name__ == 'int' (plain int, not IntEnum; contrasts with AF_INET; novel anchor)"]
    - [af_inet_cls_af,      "AF_INET.__class__.__name__.__eq__",     ["AddressFamily"], true, "socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__ == 'AddressFamily' (IntEnum member; socket_extra173 anchors; confirmed here)"]
    - [sock_stream_eq_1_b,  "SOCK_STREAM.__eq__",                    [1],               true, "socket.SOCK_STREAM == 1 (confirmed; shown for ordering: 1<2<6<17<30)"]
    - [af_inet6_eq_30_b,    "AF_INET6.__eq__",                       [30],              true, "socket.AF_INET6 == 30 (macOS/Darwin; confirmed; largest constant value in spec)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2) — standalone
#
# socket.AF_INET is 2 (IPv4 address family). AF_INET (Address Family INternet)
# is the address family constant for IPv4 sockets. Value 2 is consistent across
# all POSIX platforms.
# Novel anchor under socketconst174. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra174.AF_INET_eq_2:
  description: "socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2) == True — 2 (socket.AF_INET is the IPv4 address family constant with integer value 2; when creating an IPv4 socket you pass AF_INET as the first argument to socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM); AF_INET==2 is a POSIX standard value consistent across Linux, macOS, FreeBSD, and other POSIX systems; AF_INET is an IntEnum member of socket.AddressFamily (socket_extra173 anchors AddressFamily class identity); socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2)==True confirms the integer value; socket.AF_INET(2)==socket.SOCK_DGRAM(2): IPv4 address family and UDP datagram socket type share the value 2 — a cross-namespace coincidence; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors AF_INET.__eq__(2) under socketconst174; first socketconst174 standalone for AF_INET.__eq__(2)"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: AF_INET.__eq__
  args: [2]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) — standalone
#
# socket.SOCK_STREAM is 1 (TCP stream socket type). SOCK_STREAM provides reliable,
# ordered, connection-oriented byte streams. Value 1 on all POSIX platforms.
# SOCK_STREAM(1) < AF_INET(2): stream type constant is smaller than address family.
# Novel anchor under socketconst174. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra174.SOCK_STREAM_eq_1:
  description: "socket.SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) == True — 1 (socket.SOCK_STREAM is the stream socket type constant with integer value 1; SOCK_STREAM sockets provide reliable, connection-oriented, ordered byte stream communication — the socket type used with TCP; socket.socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM) creates a standard TCP socket; SOCK_STREAM==1 is consistent across all POSIX platforms (Linux, macOS, BSD); SOCK_STREAM(1) < AF_INET(2) by 1: the SOCK_STREAM value is 1 less than AF_INET; SOCK_STREAM(1) is the smallest socket constant in this spec: 1<2<6<17<30; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) under socketconst174; first socketconst174 standalone for SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1)"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: SOCK_STREAM.__eq__
  args: [1]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) — standalone
#
# socket.SOCK_DGRAM is 2 (UDP datagram socket type). SOCK_DGRAM sockets are
# connectionless and used for UDP. SOCK_DGRAM(2) == AF_INET(2): a cross-namespace
# coincidence.
# Novel anchor under socketconst174. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra174.SOCK_DGRAM_eq_2:
  description: "socket.SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) == True — 2 (socket.SOCK_DGRAM is the datagram socket type constant with integer value 2; SOCK_DGRAM sockets provide connectionless, unreliable datagram service — the socket type used with UDP; socket.socket(AF_INET, SOCK_DGRAM) creates a standard UDP socket; SOCK_DGRAM==2 is consistent across all POSIX platforms; SOCK_DGRAM(2) == AF_INET(2): socket type and address family constants coincidentally share the value 2 — SOCK_DGRAM is from SocketKind enum while AF_INET is from AddressFamily enum; SOCK_DGRAM(2) > SOCK_STREAM(1) by 1; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) under socketconst174; first socketconst174 standalone for SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2)"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__
  args: [2]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6) — standalone
#
# socket.IPPROTO_TCP is 6 (IANA-assigned TCP protocol number). TCP is IP protocol 6,
# assigned in RFC 790. This value is consistent across all POSIX platforms.
# Novel anchor under socketconst174. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra174.IPPROTO_TCP_eq_6:
  description: "socket.IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6) == True — 6 (socket.IPPROTO_TCP is the IP protocol number for TCP (Transmission Control Protocol); value 6 is the IANA-assigned protocol number as specified in RFC 793 and RFC 790; the IP protocol number identifies the transport layer protocol in the IP header's Protocol field; IPPROTO_TCP==6 is consistent across all POSIX platforms and is defined in the IANA Protocol Numbers registry; IPPROTO_TCP(6) > SOCK_DGRAM(2) > SOCK_STREAM(1): protocol number is larger than socket type values; IPPROTO_TCP(6) == AF_INET(2) * 3: TCP protocol number is 3 times the AF_INET value — a coincidental arithmetic relationship; novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6) under socketconst174; first socketconst174 standalone for IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6)"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__
  args: [6]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# socket.IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17) — standalone
#
# socket.IPPROTO_UDP is 17 (IANA-assigned UDP protocol number). UDP is IP protocol 17,
# assigned in RFC 790. Consistent across all POSIX platforms.
# IPPROTO_UDP(17) > IPPROTO_TCP(6) by 11.
# Novel anchor under socketconst174. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant socket_extra174.IPPROTO_UDP_eq_17:
  description: "socket.IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17) == True — 17 (socket.IPPROTO_UDP is the IP protocol number for UDP (User Datagram Protocol); value 17 is the IANA-assigned protocol number as specified in RFC 768 and RFC 790; IPPROTO_UDP==17 is consistent across all POSIX platforms and is defined in the IANA Protocol Numbers registry; IPPROTO_UDP(17) > IPPROTO_TCP(6) by 11: UDP has a higher protocol number than TCP; IPPROTO_UDP(17) < AF_INET6(30) by 13: UDP protocol number is less than the macOS/Darwin AF_INET6 value; complete constant value ordering in spec: SOCK_STREAM(1)<AF_INET(2)==SOCK_DGRAM(2)<IPPROTO_TCP(6)<IPPROTO_UDP(17)<AF_INET6(30); novel anchor: no prior socket spec anchors IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17) under socketconst174; first socketconst174 standalone for IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17)"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__
  args: [17]
  expected: true

